00:18.186 --> 00:23.524
[CRASHING SOUND]

00:23.524 --> 00:24.258
(Ronnie (voiceover))
Louisiana...
spells and voodoo dolls.

00:29.230 --> 00:33.067
A storm at the levee,
a witch in the woods.

00:34.468 --> 00:37.071
Bullshit.

00:39.039 --> 00:39.707
NAt least, that's
what I thought.

00:45.346 --> 00:49.650
I couldn't run
from the pain.

00:49.650 --> 00:52.720
None of us can.

00:52.720 --> 00:53.521
The storm at the levee...
the witch in the woods.

00:57.291 --> 00:58.126
Now I'm a believer.

01:01.662 --> 01:03.531
I believe in her.

01:21.249 --> 01:25.719
Genes spread
like a virus,

01:25.719 --> 01:27.087
npassed down through
generations.

01:34.362 --> 01:38.132
And there's no
escaping it.

01:46.740 --> 01:51.512
I hate Louisiana.

01:51.512 --> 01:52.680
I was born here,
but I'm not from here.

02:02.523 --> 02:06.327
They said, "I'm so sorry
you lost a father."

02:08.127 --> 02:10.163
I didn't lose a
father today.

02:12.466 --> 02:16.404
I lost him when
I was five.

02:16.404 --> 02:17.438
College graduation,
law school graduation...
not even a letter,

02:21.242 --> 02:24.878
not even a call.

02:26.347 --> 02:26.714
Clyde was never there
to make me a man.

02:34.154 --> 02:37.625
No, I walked
that road alone.

02:37.625 --> 02:42.363
[BELL RINGS]

02:42.363 --> 02:46.166
I don't need him, and I'm not
going to run from that. I
don't run from reality.

02:55.609 --> 03:00.614
But no matter
how far we go, inevitably,

03:00.614 --> 03:05.018
it's our choices that
determine who we become,

03:05.018 --> 03:08.422
and what becomes of us.

03:54.034 --> 03:57.705
[RECORD PLAYER SCRATCHES,
THEN BEGINS
PLAYING BLUES MUSIC]

04:39.079 --> 04:42.716
[HORROR MUSIC BEGINS PLAYING]

04:56.497 --> 05:00.368
[CRASHING SOUND]

05:35.869 --> 05:39.540
[SCREAM]

06:25.185 --> 06:28.822
Is there any way out of here?

06:31.759 --> 06:34.828
[DOOR UNLATCHES,
MUSIC IS PLAYING]

06:55.583 --> 07:00.588
[MOTOR NOISES]

07:00.588 --> 07:02.155
(Ronnie (voiceover))
This is Sheriff Steve.

07:04.725 --> 07:07.695
I've only been
here a day,

07:07.695 --> 07:10.297
but he acts
like we're best friends.

07:10.297 --> 07:11.532
In reality, he's actually
the only positive thing
about this place.

07:12.332 --> 07:16.737
(Ronnie) Morning, Steve.

07:16.737 --> 07:18.371
Oh, hey, good afternoon, Ronnie.

07:18.371 --> 07:20.574
(Ronnie) Clouds are coming in.

07:20.574 --> 07:22.576
Yeah, strange weather.

07:22.576 --> 07:23.777
What the hell
you doing up there, Ronnie?

07:25.879 --> 07:28.181
Don't do anything
you're going to regret, now.

07:28.181 --> 07:30.651
You mean something
that you'd regret.

07:30.651 --> 07:31.552
Yeah. Yeah, I guess I would
have to clean it up.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.289
[LAUGHS]

07:36.289 --> 07:38.225
Hey, you want a beer?

07:38.225 --> 07:41.261
Nah, I can't drink
while I'm on duty.

07:41.261 --> 07:42.830
Well, it was a nice
memorial service.

07:45.566 --> 07:46.967
I know y'all weren't
that close, but...

07:51.739 --> 07:52.172
(Ronnie (voiceover))
It's hard to get close

07:56.610 --> 07:57.645
when you move with your mom,
and he's not there.

08:01.615 --> 08:02.215
Worked out better.

08:06.186 --> 08:07.921
(Steve) How long
you figure on staying?

08:07.921 --> 08:09.523
(Ronnie) As long as it takes.

08:13.894 --> 08:17.197
So what's it like being
a big lawyer in the big city?

08:18.999 --> 08:20.534
I don't know.

08:24.404 --> 08:28.141
It's just what I do.

08:28.141 --> 08:29.142
I'm sorry.

08:32.913 --> 08:36.216
Fuck... unless you have kids...
you don't have any kids, do you?

08:36.216 --> 08:36.717
That's that whole
fatherhood thing.

08:39.152 --> 08:41.822
When you're a father,
you want one of two things...

08:41.822 --> 08:44.391
either have your son
carry on the family business,

08:44.391 --> 08:48.361
or carry on the family name.

08:48.361 --> 08:49.997
And you've done that...
you've done that, hands down.

08:49.997 --> 08:53.166
You're here.

08:56.369 --> 09:00.708
I'm sure he's up there, looking
down right now and smiling.
Smiling down at you.

09:00.708 --> 09:02.876
I'm sure of it.

09:02.876 --> 09:03.944
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYS]

09:12.485 --> 09:16.223
(Ronnie (voiceover))
So he was writing me letters
the whole time?

09:17.925 --> 09:18.992
It doesn't
change anything.

09:22.262 --> 09:23.631
It doesn't matter.

09:27.801 --> 09:28.736
I never got one damn
letter... that's bullshit.

09:31.438 --> 09:32.673
I'm supposed to call?

09:36.610 --> 09:36.977
I'm supposed
to come back?

09:41.682 --> 09:42.950
A son doesn't chase
his own father...
that's backwards.

09:52.926 --> 09:57.464
I don't need him.

09:57.464 --> 09:58.632
I never needed him.

10:01.234 --> 10:03.270
I got through
this on my own.

10:06.106 --> 10:10.744
I worked.

10:10.744 --> 10:11.912
I worked hard...
five graduations.

10:11.912 --> 10:17.050
He wasn't there.

10:17.050 --> 10:17.918
I didn't need him
and I don't need him now.

10:24.958 --> 10:28.628
[CRYING]

11:16.944 --> 11:20.781
[MUSIC PLAYS BACKWARD]

11:24.217 --> 11:27.687
[DOOR LATCHES]

11:32.025 --> 11:36.429
[ELECTRICAL NOISES]

11:36.429 --> 11:37.064
[DISTORTED VOICE]

11:39.199 --> 11:39.867
[DOOR CLOSES]

11:43.737 --> 11:47.975
[GROWLING]

11:47.975 --> 11:51.411
[PANICKED BREATHING]

12:03.290 --> 12:08.128
[PANICKED BREATHING]
[KNOCKING]

12:08.128 --> 12:09.196
(mysterious voice)
Good evening, Ronnie.

12:09.196 --> 12:10.197
Let me in, hon.

12:17.170 --> 12:20.774
[BANGING]

12:24.878 --> 12:28.481
[BANGING]

12:31.785 --> 12:35.789
I can smell you up there,
you stink,

12:35.789 --> 12:38.158
you stupid pig.

12:38.158 --> 12:38.792
[PANTING AND KNOCKING]

12:42.129 --> 12:45.465
You know what I want!

12:49.970 --> 12:53.773
[MOANING]

13:00.881 --> 13:04.952
[CAR STARTS]

13:04.952 --> 13:06.286
[BANGING]

13:08.421 --> 13:11.124
What I want!

13:11.124 --> 13:11.859
(Ronnie (voiceover))
The dream, the letters.

13:15.162 --> 13:15.495
What happened to my dad?

13:19.867 --> 13:21.801
What happened
to my father?

13:23.036 --> 13:23.470
I can't go.

13:27.707 --> 13:28.208
[MUSIC SWELLS,
THEN STOPS]

14:41.949 --> 14:45.919
Maybe it has something to do
with my father Clyde's death.

15:05.672 --> 15:09.442
This marks the Boulevard
of Broken Dreams... Lily.

15:13.480 --> 15:16.016
He mentioned that
in the letters.

15:18.785 --> 15:20.487
He mentioned that...
he mentioned the Boulevard
of Broken Dreams

15:20.487 --> 15:24.024
in the letters.

16:38.131 --> 16:41.768
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

16:43.170 --> 16:44.171
[MUSIC PLAYING]

17:42.629 --> 17:46.233
[CATCHING BREATH]

18:00.413 --> 18:04.717
Good afternoon, sir.

18:04.717 --> 18:06.719
My name is Joe.

18:06.719 --> 18:08.155
Good afternoon, sir.

18:11.658 --> 18:15.395
Joe... Boissier...
from the Boissier Parish.

18:19.266 --> 18:23.102
And, uh...

18:25.772 --> 18:29.209
And I was hiking...

19:11.484 --> 19:15.688
Good afternoon, sir.

19:15.688 --> 19:16.889
Uh...

19:18.791 --> 19:19.426
How can I help you?

19:20.893 --> 19:22.629
Am I interrupting something?

19:22.629 --> 19:23.896
No, no.

19:23.896 --> 19:25.665
Are you sure?

19:25.665 --> 19:26.966
Yeah, yeah,
what can I do for you?

19:26.966 --> 19:27.634
Okay, because you've
got your drawers on.

19:27.634 --> 19:29.936
Okay.

19:29.936 --> 19:32.439
What can I do for you?

19:32.439 --> 19:35.208
You're standing there in your
underwear, all right. My name
is... it's Joe.

19:35.208 --> 19:38.211
And, well, what was I doing?

19:38.211 --> 19:41.248
I was hiking... I was hiking
back here, with my group.

19:41.248 --> 19:44.684
You were hiking?

19:44.684 --> 19:47.654
Sure as shit.

19:47.654 --> 19:49.088
I didn't know anyone
hiked around here.

19:49.088 --> 19:50.823
Okay, uh... uh, so anyway,
I was with my friends...

19:56.195 --> 19:58.898
and we got separated.

20:01.234 --> 20:02.769
So, um... could I... is there
a way that I could maybe...

20:05.738 --> 20:09.976
Use my phone?

20:09.976 --> 20:10.943
Sure, thank you kindly.

20:15.515 --> 20:19.319
Yeah, sure.
Come in.

20:24.123 --> 20:28.828
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:28.828 --> 20:29.562
I'm just going to go
upstairs, grab my phone.

20:30.863 --> 20:33.833
Okay, thank you.

20:38.571 --> 20:42.442
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

20:57.590 --> 21:02.562
What's with all the titty pics?

21:02.562 --> 21:03.863
(Ronnie) I don't know...
it's my dad's place.

21:09.936 --> 21:13.740
Yeah... your dad
got a weird house.

21:16.343 --> 21:18.978
What trail were
you hiking?

21:20.547 --> 21:23.316
I don't remember.

21:23.316 --> 21:23.716
The the one back
on that ridge line.

21:25.452 --> 21:27.286
(Ronnie) Okay.

21:54.547 --> 21:59.151
I'll get you some water.

21:59.151 --> 21:59.452
(Jake)
Oh, thank you.

22:02.755 --> 22:04.424
(Ronnie) You know, the sheriff's
a good friend of mine. I'll call
him up, he'll help you find your
group.

22:04.424 --> 22:06.058
You don't got to
call the sheriff.

22:06.058 --> 22:07.226
(Ronnie) No, no, no, it's okay.

22:07.226 --> 22:08.094
He's a nice guy,
you'll like him.

22:08.094 --> 22:09.228
That's fine, thank you.

22:09.228 --> 22:11.030
No need to call the sheriff.

22:11.030 --> 22:12.899
I'll call myself.

22:12.899 --> 22:14.266
(Ronnie) He's a really good guy,
he'll help you.

22:14.266 --> 22:16.469
No, you don't need to call him.

22:16.469 --> 22:17.370
(Ronnie) It's really no trouble,
honestly.

22:17.370 --> 22:20.540
Thank you, I'll take the phone.

22:20.540 --> 22:22.675
That's fine, thank you very
much. I'm going to call my
friends. - He comes by a lot.
Don't call the sheriff, give me.

22:22.675 --> 22:24.744
He's a personal friend.
It's okay.

22:24.744 --> 22:26.513
You going to give me the phone
or not? I know him personally.

22:26.513 --> 22:28.147
Set the fucking phone down,
goddamn it.

22:28.147 --> 22:30.683
Pass me the phone.

22:31.451 --> 22:32.485
Now sit your ass down.

22:38.825 --> 22:42.595
Sit down, you ain't got to
be so slow about it.

22:44.230 --> 22:45.565
Can I put my hands down?

22:48.601 --> 22:50.102
Put them down then, shit.

22:50.102 --> 22:52.639
What do you want?

22:52.639 --> 22:53.072
I saw you out there,
digging around.

22:55.842 --> 22:57.309
You took a woman's
purse, I need it back.

22:57.309 --> 22:59.011
Purse?

23:01.313 --> 23:02.882
You don't strike
me as a purse guy.

23:02.882 --> 23:04.984
It ain't about... Fuck.
I want that goddamn purse back.

23:04.984 --> 23:08.788
I saw you out there with it,
give it back.

23:11.658 --> 23:14.827
I don't have your purse, okay?

23:17.497 --> 23:17.864
I need that purse back, now.

23:22.168 --> 23:23.470
Okay, just, just, just, just...
calm down.

23:25.638 --> 23:31.043
Okay. It's going to be fine.

23:31.043 --> 23:32.311
- I am calm.
- All right... This is calm.
Do you want to see angry?

23:32.311 --> 23:34.714
Okay, relax, relax.

23:34.714 --> 23:35.982
This isn't going to help,
but I can help you.

23:35.982 --> 23:38.551
Okay?

23:38.551 --> 23:40.219
Okay, so tell me
your master plan.

23:40.219 --> 23:41.821
How does shooting me
get your purse back?

23:55.835 --> 23:59.672
All right, then what?

24:02.975 --> 24:05.845
Something strange
is happening here...
in this house.

24:10.917 --> 24:13.920
Like what?

24:15.655 --> 24:16.255
You've got rebels out
here stealing your shit?

24:16.255 --> 24:18.991
I've seen that.

24:18.991 --> 24:20.226
It's a person.

24:21.127 --> 24:23.963
Who?

24:23.963 --> 24:24.564
I don't know.

24:25.498 --> 24:27.333
I'm sorry?

24:27.333 --> 24:28.601
Who, or she, or what.

24:29.536 --> 24:32.438
I don't care, let's go.

24:32.438 --> 24:34.907
You know, the place you saw me

24:34.907 --> 24:37.109
is the Boulevard
of Broken Dreams.

24:37.109 --> 24:39.512
I saw that on the map.

24:43.916 --> 24:48.354
(Jake)
We was in the woods,
it wasn't in the city.

24:48.354 --> 24:51.023
What are you rambling about?

24:51.023 --> 24:52.458
(Ronnie)
There's a map, and on the map

24:52.458 --> 24:53.826
is the Boulevard
of Broken Dreams,

24:53.826 --> 24:54.594
and that's where
you were.

24:55.662 --> 24:56.596
What the hell
you looking at?

25:00.567 --> 25:01.267
You're gonna to talk to me,
talk to me.

25:04.003 --> 25:06.739
You talking
to the goddamn bookshelf.

25:06.739 --> 25:08.908
My father must have
known where it was.

25:08.908 --> 25:13.580
Your father knew what?

25:13.580 --> 25:15.047
Where's your father at?
Maybe he got it.

25:15.047 --> 25:17.283
My father...

25:17.283 --> 25:18.985
Your father took my purse, then.

25:18.985 --> 25:20.820
Spit it out then, goddammit.
You're stalling now.

25:22.121 --> 25:23.723
Clyde's dead.

25:26.458 --> 25:27.560
I don't care who Clyde is.

25:28.895 --> 25:31.430
If he died, that's his problem.

25:31.430 --> 25:33.566
You've overstayed your welcome.

25:33.566 --> 25:34.901
Leave my house now.

25:36.535 --> 25:38.270
I over-what?

25:38.270 --> 25:39.706
I'm not going anywhere.

25:39.706 --> 25:40.472
You're going to help me,
right now.

25:40.472 --> 25:42.842
Get out.

25:42.842 --> 25:44.711
Get up, off your ass,
and get out of my house.

25:44.711 --> 25:47.246
Oh, you're crazy.

25:50.116 --> 25:51.784
Okay, well,
maybe beating your ass
ain't going to do nothing.

25:51.784 --> 25:56.155
But I'm going to
do it anyway.

25:56.155 --> 25:57.690
[FIGHTING SOUNDS]

26:06.432 --> 26:10.002
(Jake)
Get back here.

26:55.214 --> 26:59.051
There's a photo
thing in that purse.

26:59.819 --> 27:01.654
A little girl made it.

27:04.256 --> 27:06.926
I've got to get it back.

27:25.778 --> 27:30.382
I don't think we
should go out there.

27:30.382 --> 27:33.585
It's all gonna be
snakes and shit...

27:33.585 --> 27:35.722
don't know what
we're walking into.

27:35.722 --> 27:36.422
It's Louisiana...
there's snakes.

27:38.891 --> 27:42.729
That's not what I mean.

27:42.729 --> 27:45.932
Don't know if Jake's got
something planned out there,
or where he went...

27:45.932 --> 27:47.734
I think it's just stupid
to walk into something

27:50.169 --> 27:51.270
without knowing
what we're walking into.

27:52.872 --> 27:53.239
Yeah... maybe you should go.

27:58.310 --> 28:02.581
Want to go home?

28:02.581 --> 28:04.784
Hey, give him the keys.

28:07.820 --> 28:12.624
Take the keys.

28:12.624 --> 28:14.493
Go home...
we'll get a ride home.

28:14.493 --> 28:17.263
I know these
woods real well.

28:17.263 --> 28:18.831
Want to go?

28:21.367 --> 28:22.268
Give me that gun, now.

28:24.804 --> 28:26.538
I'll take it.

28:26.538 --> 28:27.006
How long we gonna be out there?

28:29.842 --> 28:31.710
For a while.

28:34.346 --> 28:35.314
As long as it takes.

28:37.283 --> 28:38.751
Stop fidgeting.

28:49.095 --> 28:52.865
Where in the world
you go, Jake?

28:55.667 --> 28:59.071
[MUSIC PLAYING]

29:20.726 --> 29:25.364
Okay.

29:25.364 --> 29:26.132
What is this thing
you're sitting on?

29:29.969 --> 29:30.937
I'm not sure.

29:34.606 --> 29:35.808
It was here when
I got here.

29:39.378 --> 29:41.413
Look like somebody
trying to put up a circus.

29:51.157 --> 29:56.028
Why come you just run
out the house like that?

29:56.028 --> 29:57.897
I could have shot you
right in the back.

30:00.432 --> 30:02.801
With an empty gun?

30:02.801 --> 30:05.737
Good plan.

30:05.737 --> 30:06.939
You are a smarty-pants.

30:08.941 --> 30:10.843
It was unloaded.

30:12.879 --> 30:13.913
My apologies
for the unloaded gun...

30:17.416 --> 30:21.187
and pushing you
in the pool like that.

30:27.093 --> 30:31.797
You know, where I'm from,
a man

30:31.797 --> 30:33.465
usually accepts
another man's apology.

30:33.465 --> 30:37.036
Why are you here?

30:37.036 --> 30:37.870
I told you why.
I need something.

30:40.739 --> 30:44.510
I don't have your purse.

30:44.510 --> 30:45.344
Look, I'm...
I'm just going to
wait around a little bit, okay?

30:49.148 --> 30:52.919
You can sit there if you want,
but I need to stay.

30:56.889 --> 30:57.990
I ain't no trouble.

31:01.727 --> 31:02.394
I can't even load a gun.

31:20.279 --> 31:24.783
(Ronnie) You want to stay,
then I need your help.

31:24.783 --> 31:28.220
There are things occurring here

31:28.220 --> 31:28.955
that I just don't have
a rational explanation for.

31:30.889 --> 31:31.190
I'll help you find
what you need,

31:35.794 --> 31:37.829
but then you have to help me
figure out what's going on.

31:37.829 --> 31:39.465
(Jake) So if I help you,

31:42.601 --> 31:44.570
you're going
to help me get my purse back?

31:44.570 --> 31:46.005
(Ronnie) Come here,
let me show you something.

32:07.926 --> 32:11.630
This is what she wants.

32:19.638 --> 32:23.442
How the hell did a witch
own the land, anyhow?

32:33.052 --> 32:37.689
(Ronnie) One more thing
to show you.

32:37.689 --> 32:38.657
I think it
ties everything together.

32:38.657 --> 32:40.326
Let me grab my rifle.

32:43.262 --> 32:47.133
Where the hell we goin'?

33:05.884 --> 33:09.555
Ain't nothing out here
but photo things,
but no photos in 'em.

33:18.197 --> 33:22.634
It's out here somewhere.

33:22.634 --> 33:23.535
You don't see it?

33:28.240 --> 33:31.377
(Ronnie) You know, I still don't
know what you're looking for.
It's a goddamn purse.

33:31.377 --> 33:32.511
(Ronnie) Big, small...

33:32.511 --> 33:33.779
It's pink.

33:33.779 --> 33:35.114
Like a girl's purse.

33:56.001 --> 34:00.839
I've done my part.

34:00.839 --> 34:01.707
I told you the purse
wasn't here, or I don't have it.

34:28.065 --> 34:31.703
You all right?

34:39.978 --> 34:43.614
My name ain't Joe.

34:44.516 --> 34:45.117
It's Jake.

34:49.855 --> 34:50.856
Jake Simons.

34:59.331 --> 35:03.101
You ever wonder how you got
to a certain point?

35:12.544 --> 35:16.648
Yeah.

35:16.648 --> 35:17.649
We're here now.

35:20.886 --> 35:21.753
(Ronnie) I know it sounds crazy,
but there it is.

35:23.622 --> 35:26.758
You can use my help,
I can use yours.

35:26.758 --> 35:28.460
Now it's up to you.

35:31.463 --> 35:35.867
(Jake) You got
anything to drink?

35:35.867 --> 35:39.405
I don't care what it is.

35:39.405 --> 35:41.139
Shit, I'll drink cheap
scotch from a gas station.

35:45.344 --> 35:49.248
[NATURE SOUNDS]

36:14.873 --> 36:18.544
[GROANS]

36:53.879 --> 36:57.516
God damn it.

37:35.954 --> 37:39.958
Yup.

37:39.958 --> 37:40.792
Okay.

37:46.598 --> 37:50.436
(Ronnie) You get enough
to drink last night?

37:56.675 --> 38:00.412
I bet you already
called the sheriff.

38:11.790 --> 38:16.127
Hey.

38:16.127 --> 38:16.795
What's your problem, boy?

38:18.530 --> 38:20.699
(man 2) I don't have a problem.

38:20.699 --> 38:23.301
No?

38:26.304 --> 38:30.876
Okay.

38:30.876 --> 38:31.577
What do you know
about this creek, then?

38:34.045 --> 38:37.549
It ain't just a creek,
it's man made.

38:37.549 --> 38:41.853
Somebody diverting
water somewhere...

38:41.853 --> 38:45.591
probably from that lake
a mile up.

38:45.591 --> 38:47.092
Which way would he go,
if, uh... he was running away.

38:52.964 --> 38:57.135
Which way would you go?

38:57.135 --> 38:59.638
I'd go east.

38:59.638 --> 39:00.071
Excuse... I think there's
a boot print there.

39:05.844 --> 39:10.081
See it, there?

39:10.081 --> 39:11.016
Hey, way to go, Twiggy.

39:13.652 --> 39:16.622
He done something right.

39:18.256 --> 39:19.425
Even a dog can find a dog turd.

39:19.425 --> 39:20.792
[SOUND OF RUNNING WATER]

39:41.312 --> 39:45.584
What are you doing
over there?

39:45.584 --> 39:47.519
(Ronnie) I'm researching.

39:52.991 --> 39:57.262
(Jake)
Well I don't goddamn research,
I'll tell you that.

39:57.262 --> 39:59.698
I don't research.

39:59.698 --> 40:01.032
I do... I do shit.

40:04.369 --> 40:05.737
I'ma make it happen.

40:08.774 --> 40:10.909
I'm not sitting here all day.

40:16.715 --> 40:20.486
Sitting here
ain't helping nobody.

40:24.656 --> 40:28.994
Can we lose the music?

40:28.994 --> 40:31.329
(Ronnie) Hey.

40:31.329 --> 40:33.565
Hey, come look at this.

40:33.565 --> 40:35.667
(Jake) I don't have time
for no games.

40:35.667 --> 40:37.035
(Ronnie) No, no,
no, no, no.

40:37.035 --> 40:40.038
(Jake) We're gonna
get this bitch.

40:40.038 --> 40:43.208
Listen, we have to look at
this... I'll put a bullet right
in her head. - Look at this,
okay? No I'm not looking at.

40:43.208 --> 40:44.543
We're going out there,
and you're going to show me
where my stuff is.

40:44.543 --> 40:47.112
This is what's going
to get your purse back.

40:47.112 --> 40:48.446
You know these woods
better than I do,
don't just fucking sit there.

40:48.446 --> 40:49.681
This is how we're
going to trap her.

40:49.681 --> 40:51.883
(Jake) I'm going, get up.

40:51.883 --> 40:53.318
Joe, just sit down,
and we'll work it out.

40:53.318 --> 40:54.953
I'm leaving, I'm
up out of here.

40:54.953 --> 40:56.021
Damn it, Joe!

40:56.021 --> 40:57.122
Sit down!

41:04.095 --> 41:07.733
That's good.

41:09.434 --> 41:09.668
Okay.

41:20.679 --> 41:25.450
What you got to say, man?

41:25.450 --> 41:26.484
Look, I'm sorry
I lost my cool, okay?

41:29.588 --> 41:32.223
I can't lift this.
I need your help.

41:32.223 --> 41:34.693
What is that?

41:34.693 --> 41:36.194
It's the platform
we were on.

41:36.194 --> 41:39.330
You see the siren?

41:39.330 --> 41:41.466
This lets us know she's here.

41:41.466 --> 41:45.170
We put gas there...

41:45.170 --> 41:46.705
(Jake) That don't make no
goddamn sense to nobody.

41:48.306 --> 41:51.076
What is this right here?

41:51.076 --> 41:53.378
(Ronnie) It says
motion detector.

41:53.378 --> 41:55.346
What is this pulley?

41:55.346 --> 41:56.381
What does any of this do?

41:56.381 --> 41:59.618
It burns her.

41:59.618 --> 42:00.251
This look like
a goddamn mess to me...

42:02.187 --> 42:04.656
charts, writings,

42:04.656 --> 42:07.225
I don't understand none of that.

42:07.225 --> 42:09.460
You tell me what this is.

42:09.460 --> 42:11.162
I don't know exactly what
it is, but look at this.

42:11.162 --> 42:14.432
That's her, right?

42:14.432 --> 42:15.934
You see that?

42:15.934 --> 42:17.035
You think I'm stupid.

42:18.303 --> 42:19.638
I...

42:22.874 --> 42:26.111
(Jake) You explain to me how
that's supposed to help me.
Just... just work with me on it.

42:26.111 --> 42:28.914
We'll get it.

42:28.914 --> 42:30.649
It'll just take a little
while. You know what I think
about you, Ronnie Baker?

42:30.649 --> 42:32.818
I think you
a goddamn coward.

42:32.818 --> 42:34.185
You don't ever call me
fucking stupid again.

42:34.185 --> 42:36.154
You got that?

42:36.154 --> 42:36.788
You're stalling.

42:38.489 --> 42:39.758
You're full of shit,
and I'm fucking out of here.

42:39.758 --> 42:41.660
(Ronnie)
Hey, I'm not a coward.

42:44.029 --> 42:46.497
Yeah, whatever.

42:46.497 --> 42:47.733
Thanks for the information.

42:47.733 --> 42:49.167
Hey, Ronnie.

42:49.167 --> 42:51.069
Hey, Steve.

42:51.069 --> 42:52.738
How are you?

42:52.738 --> 42:54.640
Oh, the usual.

42:54.640 --> 42:57.075
You know.

42:57.075 --> 42:58.677
You all right?

43:01.279 --> 43:03.048
Yeah.
Yeah, yeah.

43:03.048 --> 43:05.416
Fine.

43:05.416 --> 43:07.452
Is this your friend?

43:07.452 --> 43:08.353
Yeah, this is, uh...
this is Harold,
a childhood friend of mine.

43:09.487 --> 43:13.458
Oh, okay.

43:13.458 --> 43:15.293
Nice.

43:15.293 --> 43:15.727
Never seen him around.

43:17.295 --> 43:19.264
Harold, is it, huh?

43:19.264 --> 43:22.100
Hello, sir.

43:22.100 --> 43:22.868
So y'all going to do
a little hunting, or shooting?

43:26.304 --> 43:27.739
Rabbit hunting.

43:30.809 --> 43:32.010
Rabbit hunting?
I'll be damned.

43:32.010 --> 43:34.880
Really?

43:34.880 --> 43:35.714
Boy, you shoot a rabbit
with that big old gun,

43:37.916 --> 43:40.418
and you're going to
send his furry ass

43:40.418 --> 43:41.186
to hell in about
50 pieces.

43:41.953 --> 43:43.755
[SHEEPISH LAUGHTER]

43:46.491 --> 43:49.460
Yeah... Yes sir, no shit.

43:49.460 --> 43:50.996
I'll... let me run inside,
and I'll grab the .22.

43:58.970 --> 44:03.208
(Steve) That makes sense.

44:03.208 --> 44:04.142
Sure does.

44:12.450 --> 44:17.155
Ronnie Boy.

44:17.155 --> 44:18.023
We had a little incident
last night in town.

44:21.326 --> 44:24.062
And... I don't want
to alarm you, or anything,

44:24.062 --> 44:27.665
but a girl was hurt pretty bad.

44:27.665 --> 44:28.767
Well, I just come out here
to see if you may have...

44:43.882 --> 44:49.287
So, we're still
gathering information.

44:49.287 --> 44:50.722
Just kind of wondering
if you knew anything,
or heard anything,

44:52.123 --> 44:56.895
or if anybody come knocking
at you?

44:56.895 --> 44:58.129
No, just...
just me and Harold.

44:58.930 --> 45:01.767
Harold, huh?

45:08.239 --> 45:12.577
What?

45:12.577 --> 45:13.044
Did my-my dad ever, uh...

45:14.780 --> 45:15.847
did you ever respond
to any calls from here?

45:20.986 --> 45:22.153
Why do you ask that?

45:25.891 --> 45:27.625
I was looking through
some of his stuff,

45:27.625 --> 45:30.261
and there's some
really odd things.

45:30.261 --> 45:33.899
So I was kind of curious
if he called, or said anything.

45:38.970 --> 45:40.471
Well, I wasn't
going to mention it.

45:43.674 --> 45:46.978
When your daddy
started making calls

45:46.978 --> 45:48.914
to the station about some
lady or some old woman

45:48.914 --> 45:51.649
going through his stuff
or stealing things,

45:51.649 --> 45:55.120
we didn't think much of it.

45:55.120 --> 45:58.023
But, uh... I guess the boys
thought he was joking around, so
they started calling him Crazy
Clyde

45:58.023 --> 45:59.791
and all kinds of stuff.

45:59.791 --> 46:01.626
You thought he was crazy?

46:01.626 --> 46:02.828
No, I didn't say that.

46:02.828 --> 46:05.430
I didn't say that.

46:05.430 --> 46:06.764
Well, did you come
to check, to verify what he was
complaining about?

46:09.367 --> 46:14.339
We try to keep an
open mind about things.

46:14.339 --> 46:17.542
They say if you don't blink
you won't miss it.

46:17.542 --> 46:18.910
So I try not to blink.

46:19.610 --> 46:20.545
Oh, hey.

46:24.215 --> 46:24.850
Well, I'll check
back with you later.

46:27.853 --> 46:29.888
See ya.

46:51.676 --> 46:55.780
Childhood friend, my ass.

46:55.780 --> 46:57.215
[CAR STARTING]

47:01.452 --> 47:05.156
[MUSIC PLAYING]

47:30.615 --> 47:35.286
(Ronnie (voiceover))
When the sheriff told me
a girl got hurt,

47:35.286 --> 47:39.824
I started piecing
the puzzle together

47:39.824 --> 47:43.028
with Jake and the purse,
and some guys he mentioned.

47:43.028 --> 47:47.432
I don't know...
Jake doesn't strike me

47:47.432 --> 47:51.269
as one who could really
do something that bad,

47:51.269 --> 47:53.771
so I figured I need him
as much as he needs me.

47:53.771 --> 47:56.507
So I decided
not to say anything.

47:58.443 --> 47:59.410
And thank goodness I didn't,
because this night
changed everything.

48:18.196 --> 48:22.033
[STRANGE BREATHING
SOUNDS]

48:28.206 --> 48:32.043
[MYSTERIOUS VOICE]

48:33.611 --> 48:35.113
(witch) Ronnie.

49:09.347 --> 49:13.151
[FALLING SOUNDS]
Ah!

50:00.598 --> 50:04.402
(witch) Are you mad
about the purse?

50:06.537 --> 50:07.605
I'll leave it here
on the floor for you.

50:11.242 --> 50:14.279
(shouting)
On the floor, Ronnie!

50:14.279 --> 50:17.215
I love you, Ronnie.

50:29.260 --> 50:33.098
I hate you, Ronnie.

50:34.099 --> 50:36.167
I hate you, Ronnie.

50:38.903 --> 50:40.338
Get off my land!

51:09.667 --> 51:13.371
Oh come on, Goddamn it.

51:18.643 --> 51:22.280
[STRAINING]

51:25.283 --> 51:29.086
She could have killed me.

51:36.794 --> 51:40.498
[MUSIC PLAYING]

51:51.642 --> 51:55.280
Look at me.

51:59.950 --> 52:03.588
Look at me.

52:04.989 --> 52:05.390
I hate you!

52:32.817 --> 52:37.655
I'm surprised
you're still here.

52:37.655 --> 52:38.656
(Jake) Somebody had
to make sure you...

52:41.192 --> 52:44.262
didn't choke on
your own spit.

52:44.262 --> 52:45.430
If my head wasn't spinning,
I'd mistake your crassness
as maybe caring.

52:50.401 --> 52:51.269
[EERIE AMBIENCE SWELLS]

53:00.478 --> 53:04.282
[SMASHING SOUNDS]

53:09.420 --> 53:13.258
(Jake) Aw, come on.

53:18.429 --> 53:22.199
(Ronnie) I told you
what we have to do.

53:27.905 --> 53:31.509
You don't listen.

53:33.478 --> 53:33.744
Baker, check that out.

53:40.885 --> 53:44.955
It's empty.

53:44.955 --> 53:45.856
(Jake) Look closer.

53:52.363 --> 53:57.034
Lad looks real young.

53:57.034 --> 53:58.369
And that girl's
prairie chicken for sure.

54:23.260 --> 54:27.598
(Ronnie)
We've got to build it, man.

54:27.598 --> 54:29.367
We gotta finish the contraption.

54:30.801 --> 54:31.536
I know you hate it,
but we've got to do it.

54:35.239 --> 54:36.741
There isn't another way.

54:39.777 --> 54:41.045
(Jake) There's got to be a
better option. (Ronnie) There's
not.

54:42.947 --> 54:47.117
Is this working for you?

54:47.117 --> 54:47.685
I don't know
what else to do.

54:49.520 --> 54:51.456
Listen, I don't know, um...

54:55.426 --> 54:57.728
exactly what to do, but...

55:00.665 --> 55:02.333
There's got to be
a better option.

55:05.202 --> 55:06.804
Well... Clyde knew what to do.

55:09.574 --> 55:14.178
He wrote that elaborate
contraption, the plans.

55:14.178 --> 55:17.181
He even built half of it.

55:17.181 --> 55:19.650
That's the way.

55:19.650 --> 55:21.486
Dammit.

55:23.421 --> 55:24.321
(Ronnie) It's the only way.

55:26.491 --> 55:26.857
So trust me.

55:30.695 --> 55:32.363
Okay.

55:34.699 --> 55:35.500
There is no other way.

55:42.139 --> 55:45.910
(Jake) After the first night,
why didn't you just leave?

55:47.612 --> 55:51.382
(Ronnie) I had a professor
who said there's...

55:55.052 --> 55:55.553
no such things
as a mystery.

56:00.391 --> 56:01.125
Every phenomenon has
some explanation.

56:05.329 --> 56:07.364
The question is, how far
are you willing to go to
discover it?

56:12.970 --> 56:15.473
You sound like
you went to college.

56:18.075 --> 56:19.043
(Ronnie) You sound like you
dropped out of high school.

56:25.249 --> 56:29.854
I did.

56:29.854 --> 56:30.488
I only made it
to the second year.

56:32.590 --> 56:34.525
I used to run
with these older kids,

56:37.327 --> 56:39.530
and they knew
about this old man...
had some battery thing,

56:44.602 --> 56:47.404
so we broke into his
house, and we stole it.

56:49.974 --> 56:52.042
I remember sitting on my bed,
that thing in my lap,

56:55.680 --> 56:59.484
and this force...

57:02.587 --> 57:04.555
come over me, like...

57:08.125 --> 57:09.794
what did you just do?

57:13.998 --> 57:14.565
So I dropped it
back on his porch.

57:19.737 --> 57:20.638
And I knocked, and I ran.

57:29.780 --> 57:33.551
When those kids found
out what I'd done...

57:35.520 --> 57:36.621
they were pissed off,
for sure.

57:43.761 --> 57:48.298
And I was scared of them.

57:48.298 --> 57:49.700
(Ronnie) So you never went back?

57:51.769 --> 57:52.670
(Jake) No, I never went back.

57:57.908 --> 58:01.646
Who do you think
is in this photo?

58:05.449 --> 58:09.086
Well, that's Clyde, for sure.

58:10.555 --> 58:11.589
That girl looks real young.

58:27.538 --> 58:31.075
Hey, come look at
this for a second.

58:35.646 --> 58:39.550
What does this look like to you?

58:41.251 --> 58:42.119
You know, you like an idiot
out here in all those clothes,

58:45.522 --> 58:48.826
in this heat.

58:48.826 --> 58:50.861
You know, Clyde taught me
only a few things,

58:50.861 --> 58:53.831
and one of them was,
was when you leave the house,

58:53.831 --> 58:57.902
wear your Sunday best.

58:57.902 --> 58:58.769
Now tell me
what this looks like.

59:01.038 --> 59:03.674
It's obviously a box, right?

59:03.674 --> 59:05.342
See?
It's a box.

59:05.342 --> 59:07.778
Okay.

59:07.778 --> 59:08.879
But what are the springs for?

59:08.879 --> 59:10.047
You're supposed
to attach it to it.

59:12.482 --> 59:14.585
Spring into place.

59:14.585 --> 59:15.620
Somebody's supposed
to go in there.

59:21.525 --> 59:25.229
[MUSIC PLAYING]

59:49.787 --> 59:53.658
One, two, three.

01:00:09.039 --> 01:00:13.844
We're sure we want to do this?

01:00:13.844 --> 01:00:15.512
Jake's been
like a brother to us.

01:00:15.512 --> 01:00:16.947
Hey, Skinny.

01:00:16.947 --> 01:00:18.949
Just shoot the fucking gun.

01:00:18.949 --> 01:00:20.751
Oh shit.

01:00:22.252 --> 01:00:23.620
Goddamn right.

01:00:24.288 --> 01:00:26.623
[GUN COCKS]

01:00:26.623 --> 01:00:27.758
Adios, Jake.

01:00:29.426 --> 01:00:30.160
[GUN SHOTS]
[CRIES OF PAIN]

01:00:31.528 --> 01:00:33.931
[FALLING SOUNDS]

01:00:33.931 --> 01:00:34.799
Now, go, stay low.
Stay low.

01:00:37.367 --> 01:00:37.902
Go inside the house,
distract him.

01:01:17.842 --> 01:01:21.712
Hey, Skinny, go in there
and turn it on.

01:01:22.579 --> 01:01:26.984
All right.

01:01:26.984 --> 01:01:27.684
I'm going to see Jake inside.

01:01:29.720 --> 01:01:31.555
Help out Skinny.

01:01:31.555 --> 01:01:32.122
Okay.

01:01:35.125 --> 01:01:39.463
Shit.

01:01:39.463 --> 01:01:41.165
All right, just wait here.

01:01:41.165 --> 01:01:42.800
All right, they're coming.

01:01:42.800 --> 01:01:44.268
All right, I'll kick his ass.

01:01:44.268 --> 01:01:45.135
I'll kick his ass good,
all right.

01:01:45.135 --> 01:01:46.570
Yep.

01:01:46.570 --> 01:01:47.772
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING]

01:02:13.063 --> 01:02:17.401
Well, good evening.

01:02:17.401 --> 01:02:19.369
Where's Jake?

01:02:19.369 --> 01:02:20.938
We saw him in here.

01:02:20.938 --> 01:02:23.974
Well, Jake left.

01:02:23.974 --> 01:02:25.475
Y'all scared the shit
out of him.

01:02:25.475 --> 01:02:27.812
Well, where'd he go?

01:02:27.812 --> 01:02:29.780
He went that way.

01:02:29.780 --> 01:02:33.583
Well what the hell's out there?

01:02:33.583 --> 01:02:36.320
Out there?

01:02:36.320 --> 01:02:37.287
Oh, witches, snakes,
gators, Jake.

01:02:42.292 --> 01:02:46.831
You just tell me
where Jake Simons is,

01:02:46.831 --> 01:02:48.765
and you don't need to get hurt.

01:02:48.765 --> 01:02:49.867
Do you need a lantern?

01:02:51.869 --> 01:02:53.170
No, I do not need
a goddamn lantern.

01:02:53.170 --> 01:02:55.772
Would you like
to read a great book?

01:02:55.772 --> 01:02:59.743
No, I don't want
to read a great book.

01:02:59.743 --> 01:03:01.045
Shut your fucking mouth,
and tell me

01:03:01.045 --> 01:03:02.012
where Jake Simons is,
right now.

01:03:06.616 --> 01:03:06.884
Oh, hi.

01:03:11.555 --> 01:03:13.790
Hope you don't mind me
coming in your humble abode.

01:03:13.790 --> 01:03:16.093
Door was open,
I took the liberty.

01:03:16.093 --> 01:03:16.927
Would you mind if we
drop your music a little?

01:03:18.628 --> 01:03:20.464
No, I love this record.

01:03:22.666 --> 01:03:25.502
Hm.

01:03:41.751 --> 01:03:45.722
[MUSIC STOPS]

01:03:45.722 --> 01:03:47.925
Hm.

01:03:51.295 --> 01:03:54.932
Hm.

01:03:55.665 --> 01:03:56.000
Don't touch that.

01:04:08.913 --> 01:04:12.549
Robert E. Lee.

01:04:36.406 --> 01:04:40.644
We're just looking
for a friend of ours.

01:04:40.644 --> 01:04:42.412
Saw him in here.

01:04:45.082 --> 01:04:45.983
Where he at?

01:04:53.223 --> 01:04:57.827
Well, like I was telling
your employee...

01:04:57.827 --> 01:05:00.264
I ain't his Goddamn employee.

01:05:00.264 --> 01:05:01.932
Please, adults are speaking.

01:05:03.133 --> 01:05:04.501
Forgive me, you were saying?

01:05:07.304 --> 01:05:09.239
He left.

01:05:09.239 --> 01:05:11.241
Really?

01:05:11.241 --> 01:05:13.043
Hm.

01:05:14.011 --> 01:05:14.979
Where he at?

01:05:16.113 --> 01:05:16.981
Why he leave?

01:05:18.348 --> 01:05:20.084
We just want to...
uh, talk to him.

01:05:20.084 --> 01:05:22.352
He probably left
because of the gunfire.

01:05:24.488 --> 01:05:27.824
Yeah, maybe.

01:05:27.824 --> 01:05:30.194
Jake has something
of ours.

01:05:32.496 --> 01:05:33.998
We just want to talk
to him about it, that's all.

01:05:38.368 --> 01:05:41.571
Well, like I said,
he's... he went that way.

01:05:41.571 --> 01:05:45.109
Oh, okay.

01:05:45.109 --> 01:05:47.144
Now... why didn't you run?

01:05:51.748 --> 01:05:53.650
Well, were you shooting at me?

01:05:55.719 --> 01:05:59.123
[LAUGHS]

01:05:59.123 --> 01:05:59.689
Oh, no... maybe.

01:06:03.560 --> 01:06:07.097
Mm.

01:06:10.467 --> 01:06:15.272
See...

01:06:15.272 --> 01:06:16.140
Make a deal with somebody,
don't freak out midway.

01:06:21.245 --> 01:06:25.049
Grab her purse, and then
run off, like a little bitch.

01:06:27.684 --> 01:06:29.253
Okay, thank you.

01:06:31.955 --> 01:06:33.457
I'll remember that.

01:06:33.457 --> 01:06:34.991
Please do.

01:06:36.160 --> 01:06:37.427
Now, where is the purse?

01:06:46.603 --> 01:06:50.907
Don't make me ask twice.

01:06:50.907 --> 01:06:52.076
I loathe asking twice.

01:06:55.212 --> 01:06:59.049
Right there.

01:07:00.117 --> 01:07:00.450
That was easy.

01:07:09.193 --> 01:07:13.097
I'll watch him.

01:07:59.276 --> 01:08:04.114
(Ronnie) There's no money in it.

01:08:04.114 --> 01:08:05.149
A witch, Lily Grace...
she has it.

01:08:11.721 --> 01:08:15.392
[LAUGHS]

01:08:17.993 --> 01:08:22.232
You bat shit, boy?

01:08:22.232 --> 01:08:24.568
There ain't no witches.

01:08:24.568 --> 01:08:26.569
No?

01:08:26.569 --> 01:08:28.938
Okay.

01:08:28.938 --> 01:08:29.305
The boss man says stay here.

01:08:30.573 --> 01:08:32.176
Just wait here for a minute.

01:08:32.176 --> 01:08:34.211
All right, he'll come out.

01:08:34.211 --> 01:08:35.179
Kick his ass, all right?

01:08:35.179 --> 01:08:36.845
Kick his ass.

01:08:36.845 --> 01:08:38.046
This dude ain't
going to tell us shit.

01:08:38.046 --> 01:08:40.116
Okay.

01:08:42.018 --> 01:08:42.652
Hey, hey,
there's Jake out there.

01:08:46.189 --> 01:08:48.457
Go get him.

01:09:15.852 --> 01:09:19.488
Hey, Skinny!

01:09:31.134 --> 01:09:35.805
Shit, who... hey, who is that?

01:09:35.805 --> 01:09:39.343
Come back...
what the hell's going on?

01:09:39.343 --> 01:09:41.711
Yo, where's everybody going?

01:09:52.689 --> 01:09:57.193
No, stay here, stay here,
all right?

01:09:57.193 --> 01:09:58.228
Boss man says stay here, okay?

01:11:54.043 --> 01:11:58.281
Hey, boss man, you in here?

01:11:58.281 --> 01:11:59.683
Can't see a damn thing.

01:12:07.424 --> 01:12:11.060
[DOOR CREAKS]

01:12:18.935 --> 01:12:22.606
[ALARM GOES OFF]

01:12:26.776 --> 01:12:31.114
Ow!

01:12:31.114 --> 01:12:31.781
Holy shit, what the hell?

01:12:33.450 --> 01:12:36.119
What the hell is this?

01:12:36.119 --> 01:12:36.886
Bright lights.
It's like sixth of July in here.

01:12:50.500 --> 01:12:54.137
Hey, Twiggy.

01:12:56.973 --> 01:13:01.310
Oh shit, what the hell
is wrong with you?

01:13:01.310 --> 01:13:04.881
(witch) Who are you?

01:13:04.881 --> 01:13:05.615
Another bastard here
to steal from me?

01:13:08.585 --> 01:13:10.119
No, no, no, I'm here...
I'm here for Jake.

01:13:10.119 --> 01:13:12.121
That's it.

01:13:12.121 --> 01:13:13.289
(witch) Get out of here!

01:13:13.289 --> 01:13:14.724
You get out of here.

01:13:17.761 --> 01:13:19.062
Listen,
I don't want to hurt you.

01:13:19.062 --> 01:13:21.531
Ah! Jesus!

01:13:21.531 --> 01:13:22.599
[CRACKING SOUND]

01:14:12.415 --> 01:14:16.520
Jake!

01:14:16.520 --> 01:14:17.621
Goddamn it.

01:14:17.621 --> 01:14:19.523
Where you at, boy?

01:14:30.033 --> 01:14:33.803
(witch) You smell like you've
had a rough night, young man.

01:14:34.604 --> 01:14:38.241
You did this?

01:14:40.877 --> 01:14:44.113
[HEAVY, LABORED BREATHING]

01:15:09.138 --> 01:15:12.776
[SCREAMING]

01:15:17.814 --> 01:15:22.151
(Ronnie) I know what you want.

01:15:22.151 --> 01:15:23.486
Come outside.

01:15:23.486 --> 01:15:24.688
[SCARED BREATHING]

01:15:44.641 --> 01:15:48.244
Ronald, heads up!

01:15:49.779 --> 01:15:50.113
[RATTLING SOUND]

01:15:56.519 --> 01:16:00.156
It's time!

01:16:18.441 --> 01:16:22.378
Reach in.

01:16:22.378 --> 01:16:23.613
Take it.

01:16:33.089 --> 01:16:36.860
It's your fault.
I did everything I could.

01:16:44.333 --> 01:16:48.037
[CRIES OF PAIN]

01:16:50.073 --> 01:16:51.074
You lied!

01:16:54.310 --> 01:16:56.145
(Ronnie) Look at you.

01:16:56.145 --> 01:16:57.981
You wanted this.

01:16:57.981 --> 01:16:59.949
I hate you, Ronnie!

01:17:01.417 --> 01:17:03.019
Your father was a crook!

01:17:08.357 --> 01:17:12.829
You took a father from me.

01:17:12.829 --> 01:17:15.264
It's your fault.
I did everything I could.

01:17:22.005 --> 01:17:26.375
Shit!

01:17:26.375 --> 01:17:27.176
(Ronnie) She took it, Jake.

01:17:36.986 --> 01:17:41.490
(Jake)
You're a sick son of a bitch.

01:17:41.490 --> 01:17:43.092
(Ronnie) She took it, Jake.

01:17:43.092 --> 01:17:45.161
She had your purse, Jake.

01:17:45.161 --> 01:17:47.363
She had it.

01:17:47.363 --> 01:17:48.597
I helped you get it back.

01:17:48.597 --> 01:17:50.233
Oh, Ronald.

01:17:50.233 --> 01:17:51.567
Don't do this!

01:17:51.567 --> 01:17:53.436
I know you took the purse.

01:17:53.436 --> 01:17:54.971
You used me, I get it.

01:17:54.971 --> 01:17:55.805
I don't know anything
about a purse.

01:17:59.342 --> 01:18:00.443
I don't know
what you're talking...
lose my cool.

01:18:00.443 --> 01:18:02.245
It's a two man job.

01:18:02.245 --> 01:18:03.512
I can't lift this,
I need your help.

01:18:03.512 --> 01:18:04.748
Trust me, there is no other way.

01:18:04.748 --> 01:18:08.384
This isn't for you.

01:18:08.384 --> 01:18:09.318
Ronald, think about
what's happening.

01:18:09.318 --> 01:18:10.987
She killed my dad.

01:18:10.987 --> 01:18:12.756
I know it.
I have to.

01:18:12.756 --> 01:18:14.123
Only person killed Clyde
was Clyde.

01:18:15.424 --> 01:18:17.260
You saw her, Jake.

01:18:20.129 --> 01:18:21.030
Don't you understand
what this thing is?

01:18:21.030 --> 01:18:23.666
Are you saying she a witch now?

01:18:23.666 --> 01:18:25.401
This dude is loony as hell.

01:18:25.401 --> 01:18:27.837
You bat shit, boy?

01:18:27.837 --> 01:18:28.772
We try to keep an
open mind about things.

01:18:28.772 --> 01:18:30.239
You all right?

01:18:30.239 --> 01:18:31.707
Yeah.

01:18:31.707 --> 01:18:32.842
Okay, I get it.
You're crazy.

01:18:32.842 --> 01:18:34.477
Where's the purse?

01:18:34.477 --> 01:18:35.845
It's over there.

01:18:35.845 --> 01:18:37.513
That was easy.

01:18:37.513 --> 01:18:38.281
What are you scanning for?

01:18:38.281 --> 01:18:39.749
I don't know.

01:18:39.749 --> 01:18:41.384
I'll be damned.

01:18:41.384 --> 01:18:43.552
Somebody's supposed
to go in there?

01:18:43.552 --> 01:18:45.721
[SCREAMS]

01:18:47.957 --> 01:18:52.161
I won't let you do this.

01:18:52.161 --> 01:18:53.529
You're going to kill us both.

01:18:53.529 --> 01:18:56.165
Put it down.

01:18:56.165 --> 01:18:56.866
I'm not going to watch
a man do this to himself.

01:18:58.201 --> 01:19:00.403
She'll never leave us alone.

01:19:03.039 --> 01:19:06.776
She will never give up.

01:19:06.776 --> 01:19:08.744
Yes she will.

01:19:08.744 --> 01:19:09.979
You can make it stop.

01:19:09.979 --> 01:19:11.815
I was a good son.

01:19:11.815 --> 01:19:12.982
Put it down.

01:19:12.982 --> 01:19:15.885
Look at yourself!

01:19:15.885 --> 01:19:16.385
(Clyde (voiceover))
My son, Ronnie.

01:19:19.555 --> 01:19:20.790
Life can really suck.

01:19:23.226 --> 01:19:24.760
Nit's a dark and
confusing place.

01:19:26.963 --> 01:19:28.764
I'm sorry.

01:19:30.766 --> 01:19:31.167
You don't have
to forgive me.

01:19:35.004 --> 01:19:35.905
But forgive yourself.

01:19:39.843 --> 01:19:40.343
Don't let this hold
your heart hostage.

01:19:44.413 --> 01:19:45.081
Don't descend
into darkness.

01:19:49.052 --> 01:19:50.820
We all feel defeat.

01:19:54.057 --> 01:19:54.891
NEverybody has a
pain inside him.

01:19:59.028 --> 01:20:00.463
NNobody knows
exactly what to do.

01:20:03.867 --> 01:20:05.068
NMy hope is that you rise above.

01:20:09.372 --> 01:20:12.041
Be better than this...
be better than me.

01:20:14.911 --> 01:20:16.312
Be happy.

01:20:19.115 --> 01:20:20.249
Defeat her.

01:20:22.518 --> 01:20:23.219
Don't build it.

01:20:24.587 --> 01:20:25.388
NThere's always a better option.

01:20:27.823 --> 01:20:30.193
There's always
a better way.

01:20:30.193 --> 01:20:31.294
I gave a name to my pain.

01:20:34.697 --> 01:20:38.467
(Jake) Ronald, man, put it down.

01:20:38.467 --> 01:20:39.903
This ain't the answer.

01:20:39.903 --> 01:20:42.438
(Ronnie) You're a liar.

01:20:42.438 --> 01:20:43.539
And a coward.

01:20:43.539 --> 01:20:44.941
This isn't for you!

01:20:49.178 --> 01:20:52.615
Ow!

01:21:26.983 --> 01:21:31.354
(Ronnie) You ask
if she's real?

01:21:31.354 --> 01:21:32.355
I ask, is reality
an illusion?

01:21:35.058 --> 01:21:37.626
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING]

